==English==
{{wikipedia}}
===Etymology===
From French [[cheminée]] < Latin [[caminus]] < Greek ''kaminos'' ([[furnace]]).

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

#A [[vertical]] [[tube]] or [[hollow]] [[column]] used to emit [[environmentally]] [[polluting]] [[gaseous]] and solid matter (including but not limited to by-products of burning carbon or hydro-carbon based fuels); a [[flue]]
#* '''1883:''' [[w:Robert Louis Stevenson|Robert Louis Stevenson]], ''[[w:Treasure Island|Treasure Island]]''
#*: Our '''chimney''' was a square hole in the roof:  it was but a little part of the smoke that found itts way out, and the rest eddied about the house, and kept us coughing and piping the eye.  
#The [[glass]] flue [[surrounding]] the [[flame]] of an [[oil lamp]]
#(''British'') The [[smokestack]] of a [[steam]] [[locomotive]]
#A [[narrow]] [[cleft]] in a [[rock]] [[face]]

